annotation.TEXT: Well, there's a keyhole, and a message box. Let's see what that message box has to say first.
Eh, I've got tons of lives. The ghosts can keep that one.
Oh, and don't take the middle route here. As you can see, it's just a dead end, so take the lower route.
Now, that last level wasn't terribly long, so let's go check out the next level!
Careful, I wouldn't want to fall into that pit. That would be just silly.
Well, this level's been pretty cool so far...
Well, the boo ring seems to be immune to the effects of the silver P-switch, but the eerie and the big boo are totally vulnerable!
Now, while I'm in this level, there's something else that I forgot to point out that chrideedee asked about.
Okay, now for the main reason I came back here. I'm going to grab the "balloon" and use it to explore the area to the right.
Aw, and that's a "star 2" block, meaning it only contains a star if I'm already invincible. Otherwise, it just gives me a coin. So, no combo extension for me this time.
Have I seen things like taht befor? I'm trying to remember... And thanks, I will have fun!
4-life combo! And now to finish the level! How many stars can I get from the ground?
Completing that level unlocks this pipe, which leads back to the surface.
Okay, the helium is wearing off, and Mario's voice is returning to normal (not that you could tell in this game...).

...ARGH!!! Nuts! The Yoshi coins didn't show up, because I'd already collected at least five before! I'll just take out my frustration on this paragoomba! (By the way, "Goomba" is what we're calling these guys this time. Try not to get confused.)
Not much, unfortunately. A couple of ghosts start approaching from below if you wait, but that's about it. Man, I was hoping that balloon would be useful for something more...
That also messed up my double-grab. Eh, I must be near the end, as those are the last two Yoshi coins, so I'll just toss the keys forward individually.
And that's all there is to the right, but what if I try to go on the roof to my left? Will the balloon last long enough?
Nuts! Then that means it's the other one! It's always the last one I could possibly check out of the checkable items!
Careful. Don't left+right glitch myself into that wall, or I'll probably die!
Come on, get in there!
Demo count: Division by zero error
Now that was just silly!
This involves bringing this P-switch into this pipe, so bye, Yoshi!
I have patience problems sometimes.
40. Not bad at all. Interestingly, that exactly doubles my current star total.
Wow, that worked super well! So, you don't need to do anything tricky like that corner clip to hit this block! Awesome!
Then, use Yoshi to get the P-switch where I want it, then injure myself on purpose again so that I can get through the tiny gap, just like before.
I can also easily wipe out myself if I'm careless!
Alright, now let's finish this place up. I got everything over here, right? Okay, good.
Well, I can still easily wipe out the enemies with a goomba shell!
I certainly can!
D'oh! That spike top was slain by the vertical scrolling, robbing me of a combo point!
Now, back down here, if you walk all the way down this staircase...
How can I possibly open up this ? block and grab its contents without getting myself completely trapped?
Okay, and now to lick it up so that it hits the block while it's still on Yoshi's tongue!
Yep, I made it! Now let's see what's over here...
Okay, fortunately, I still had earlier ZSNES movie files where I hadn't collected the Yoshi coins yet, so let's try this again!
Whoa. Weird graphical glitch with the first key. Now, block cloning the middle block to the right (or either side one to the left) gets you an invisible goomba shell! See?
Now, there are still things to the left that I missed, so I'm going back for them!
Oops! I overdid it with the left+right trick, and of course, it killed me! (Doesn't count as a "demo" though, since I went "back in time" just to show this off.)
Now, if you're small, don't open both of these ? blocks at once. Wait until you grab the mushroom from the first one before hitting the second. This way, you can get a flower!
Hmm... I wonder if I can get Yoshi through that tiny gap with me?
And here are the remaining two Yoshi coins, so I'll just grab them and...
Oh, sweet! The MOON reappeared! Also, so did the half Yoshi coins (which are kind of necessary for the secret exit).
MOOOOOONNNNN!!! Also, collecting these half Yoshi coins turns the blocks below them invisible...
Who knows what you'd use that second vine for, but it's there if you need it.
First, go into this pit, but not too far down. Then go under the pillar to the right. The left+right trick can help while I'm down there.
You can still advance normally even without the camera moving up here.
So, be sure to join me next time, where I'll begin with this level, Yelloh heaven zone!

So, yeah. If the Yoshi coins are still present, you can collect the first row of brown blocks, but unfortunately, you can't get past the lava. However, that lava isn't actually harmful to touch. Hmm... Can I get all the coins in time?
Well, I don't think there's a "normal" exit to this place, but if anyone knows of such an exit, let me know!
Next, avoid the boo ring and eerie like usual.
Oh, and I should duck-jump into the balloon so I can fit up there.
First, let's get the P-switch to rest on top of the block... if I can...
Hmm... P-switches of both colors...
So, if I bring a P-switch into this room, could I possibly ascend further in this room than normal (going above the bones, brown blocks, and lava above)?
Whoa. What bright red platforms you have here!
nathanisbored has suggested that I hit that block with an item that's on Yoshi's tongue as he's pulling it into his mouth, so let's try that, using this same P-switch.
Gotta check every pipe, but I don't think there are any bonus rooms in this level...
And the answer is...
The invisible goomba shell is useless against the undead, but it sure works well against its owner!
Gah! I almost went 3 for 3 with that move...
Alright, get down here, paragoomba, so that I can use you to murder everything!
Continue along the upper path to get a Yoshi coin and reach this turn block, which contains a star! Alright, party time!
19-life combo! (Not counting the 1-up mushroom.) ARGH! I was so close to reaching 20! At least I was smart enough to face to the left so that I wouldn't lose Yoshi!
Which you can then hit to reveal two keys and a weird thing that acts like a balloon!

Now, while you're climbing this first staircase, the camera will be reluctant to follow you upwards, but you can make it do so by jumping while running at full speed (the cape isn't necessary for this).
Once again, I'm impatient.
However, it turns out that's not the only solution to this puzzle...
I'm too busy killing things to collect those Yoshi coins, so I'll come back for them later.
Hello, and welcome back to Chaos CompleXX! Last time, I left you all with a puzzle...
And like all proper ghost houses, there's a Yoshi ban in effect.
Demo count: 13
Alright, here we go again...
Climbing up this vine leads to blocks containing a 1-up and another vine!
4-life combo, so far...
And now, back in the present day, let's resume our quest by entering the house of the damned!
Unfortunately, I kind of want to bring the keys with me, so I'm going to have to wait until the balloon wears off...
Okay, so I got the secret exit, but where's the normal exit?
Well, the thing is... I've never found a "normal" exit in this place.
Then, you can use the blue P-switch to collect a few coins and make the springboard slightly easier to reach.
Demo count: 14
There is one possibility that I thought of checking out, so let's go do that now...
Dude! Another star! Now I can extend my previous combo!
I'll just eat up this goomba and be on my way...
You can even hold it and kick it and everything (but watch out for the resident living inside, as it will step outside after a few seconds)!
6-life combo! Nice! Now let's go back for what I missed.
If you block clone the middle invisible block to the left (or either side invisible block to the right), you get wings, which might be useful if you somehow manage to smuggle Yoshi into here.
Give me a moment... I'll be right back...
Alright, and yet another star! This is like, so totally awesome!
SEKRET FROZA? That's an interesting name. (Also, we get a sneak peek at Bowser's castle, which has a "3" on it for some reason...)

...Um, what? Okay, so this particular Yoshi coin was placed on the subscreen boundary! Hahaha! That's awesome, 'cause now I can load up on lives! ...Until I accidentally collect its upper half, at which point it stops functioning.
Actually, before I explore that possibility I came here for, let's do some block cloning!
Use the springboard to help you collect the higher up coins if needed.
I certainly can! Awesome! Now, let's hit the P-switch, and then that ? block, and collect its contents while breaking free!

And the solution is: Bring a P-switch with me (Gameboygenius was in first with this correct answer)! So, I've already gone ahead and brought this P-switch over from later on in the level. Now, let's do that corner clipping thing again...
Alright, so let's double-grab these keys and continue to the left.
Okay, so I need to find the right key. Is it... this one?
Now, with this staircase at the beginning, getting the camera to scroll up is nice, but it isn't necessary.
Um, can I even reach that 1-up block without the aid of the ledge below it?
Alright, let's avoid the stairway to death and head to the next room!
To be continued...
...you get to prematurely end your life! Awesome!
